attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is an ARM ELF binary, likely a botnet client targeting IoT devices. It exhibits several malicious behaviors, including process daemonization by redirecting I/O to `/dev/null` (in `sub_1f6ac`). The binary constructs custom network packets for command and control (C2) communication, as evidenced by the presence of the string "http/1.1" and complex logic in `sub_1bd9c`. The most significant indicator is its use of the TOR network for C2, confirmed by the explicit handling of `.onion` domains within the large networking function `sub_e6c0`.
